Yesterday morning I picked up my phone and saw a post about Jimmy Buffett, Come Monday was playing, it made me cry & I wasn't even awake, I didn't remember that was his song...

It was a strange feeling because every Labor Day weekend that rolls around, I feel like I should be on our family road trip to this old, grand hotel in Arkansas, where we made the pilgrimage to every Labor Day weekend from the time I was born until I was 18. We were really never able to take big vacations, this was it - what we looked forward to all year. 

And the one song that's part of my most favorite memories was Margaritaville - I remember being as young as 3rd grade, watching old people dance in the lobby as the hotel band played it, it always made me wanna cry, even when I was little, it made me sad. 

I hope there's still a band there and they play it tonight 💚

#JimmyBuffett - thank you for the music 🌊
